  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "Atari 2600 ROM: raw 6507 CPU code, no header, no magic. File size determines bank-switching type: 2 KB=no mapper, 4 KB=no mapper, 8 KB=F8 (most common bankswitcher), 16 KB=F6, 32 KB=F4. Reset vector at last 4 bytes of ROM (FFFC/FFFD for full 64KB address space; mirrors for smaller ROMs). The TIA chip is programmed by writing to fixed addresses 0x00-0x2C.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Check file size to determine bank-switching type: 2 KB and 4 KB need no mapper, 8 KB uses F8, 16 KB uses F6, 32 KB uses F4",
      "Read reset vector at ROM end minus 4 bytes (e.g., offset 0x07FC for 2 KB) to find game entry point",
      "Look for bank-switch hotspot accesses: F8 ROMs access 0x1FF8 and 0x1FF9; F6 ROMs access 0x1FF6-0x1FF9",
      "Identify TIA register writes (addresses 0x00-0x2C) to confirm valid Atari 2600 game code"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "Stella (cross-platform Atari 2600 emulator)",
